⚙️ Category 8: Advanced Pikaverse Engine Mechanics

More ways to stretch your V4 Engine.

71. The "Toll Booth" Node: Requires ancient_coin (amount: 5). If inventory
    doesn't have 5, portal routes to a mini-game node to earn more.
72. The Karma System: Give the player invisible items (good_karma or bad_karma)
    based on how they treat NPCs. The final boss checks which item you have and
    changes the ending!
73. The Escort Mission: You are given an item called "lost_puppy". Certain nodes
    will check if you still have it. If you step on a trap node, it removes
    "lost_puppy".
74. The VIP Lounge: A portal that only opens if the player has the item
    "fashion_badge" AND "sunglasses".
75. The Password Scavenger Hunt: 4 different nodes give the player 4 words. The
    final door is a Word Puzzle node where the answer is the 4 words combined
    (e.g., BLUE APPLE MAGIC WAND).
76. The Decoy Key: Give the player a "rusty_key". Make them think it's the right
    one. At the lock, it breaks (Effect: remove_item: rusty_key) and spawns a
    boss!
77. The Reverse Escape Room: The player starts with 10 keys. Every door they
    open requires a specific key, but if they use the wrong key, they lose it
    forever.
78. The Poison Apple: A reward node offers a shiny item. But grabbing it
    triggers an effect that subtracts 60 seconds from the global timer!
79. The Echo Chamber: 3 identical puzzle nodes in a row. The answers are the
    exact same. If they try a different answer, it loops them back to the start.
80. The VIP Bouncer: A node that checks your inventory. If you have the
    "vip_pass", it skips 5 puzzle nodes and takes you straight to the treasure.

